{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/closure"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" represents a callback supplied by the programmer."}],"kind":"symbol","relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"kind":"relationships"}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3dal7","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3g7pp","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-3sg1w","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-6iibg","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(_:)-8g8g2","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(raw:)-26247","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(raw:)-797bm","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingRaw:)-16wjq","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(retainingRaw:)-7dv4s","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/init(simple:data:)"],"anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/ptr"]},{"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/new(object:object:)","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/new(simple:data:)"]},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure\/ClosureProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Closure","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It will generally comprise a function of some kind and a marshaller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"used to call it. It is the responsibility of the marshaller to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"convert the arguments for the invocation from "},{"code":"GValues","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a suitable form, perform the callback on the converted arguments,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and transform the return value back into a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the case of C programs, a closure usually just holds a pointer"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to a function and maybe a data argument, and the marshaller"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"converts between ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Value","type":"reference"},{"text":" and native C types. The GObject","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"library provides the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/CClosure","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type for this purpose. Bindings for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other languages need marshallers which convert between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GValues"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and suitable representations in the runtime of the language in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"order to use functions written in that language as callbacks. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_closure_set_marshal()"},{"type":"text","text":" to set the marshaller on such a custom"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"closure implementation.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Within GObject, closures play an important role in the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"implementation of signals. When a signal is registered, the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"c_marshaller","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" argument to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_signal_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" specifies the default C"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"marshaller for any closure which is connected to this","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"signal. GObject provides a number of C marshallers for this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"purpose, see the g_cclosure_marshal_","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"() functions. Additional C","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"marshallers can be generated with the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"#glib-genmarshal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"utility.  Closures can be explicitly connected to signals with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_signal_connect_closure()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but it usually more convenient to let"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"GObject create a closure automatically by using one of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"g_signal_connect_","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"() functions which take a callback function\/user"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"data pair."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using closures has a number of important advantages over a simple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"callback function\/data pointer combination:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Closures allow the callee to get the types of the callback parameters,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which means that language bindings don’t have to write individual glue","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for each callback type.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The reference counting of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" makes it easy to handle reentrancy"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"right; if a callback is removed while it is being invoked, the closure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and its parameters won’t be freed until the invocation finishes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"g_closure_invalidate()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and invalidation notifiers allow callbacks to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"automatically removed when the objects they point to go away."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GClosure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ClosureRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Closure"},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GClosure"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","title":"Closure","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Closure"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Closure"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"externalID":"s:10GLibObject7ClosureC"},"sections":[],"re